    "description": "<i>&quot;The Last Will&quot; is a short yet intense adventure game about a grieving father who finds out his estranged son has left him a very special Will. His quest is to fulfill it with an assistant, despite his prejudices.</i><br><br>Presented for the first time in 1080p, &quot;The Last Will&quot; is a 3D point-and-click dramatic adventure game played from the perspective of a grieving father whose son just passed away.  &quot;The Last Will&quot; intertwines a sad (and uplifting) narrative with puzzle-solving gameplay as well as finding hidden items to complete achievements. <br><br>Using your mouse, you will click (or double click to run) to decide where you want your 3D character to move to, in a 3D world with fixed cameras. Most of the gameplay is going from point A to point B in order to make the story go forward, but at certain times, you will need to find a way to solve a casual puzzle (find a way to solve a kitten, or find a missing briefcase). <br>Although the game is short, you can always save your game to save your progression as well as changing the game options (sounds and music) to your convinence.<br><br>Featuring an emotional soundtrack and high quality sounds, &quot;The Last Will&quot; is an intense adventure game drama about the bonds between a father and his son.",
